      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5707"> </a>It is necessary to check the air-gap between the speed sensor and the phonic wheel, once the components are refitted.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5709"> </a>For this purpose, use a feeler gauge to check the air-gap; then, carry out 4 measures of the air-gap, one every 90Â° of wheel
            turn.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_007803246.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_012203247.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5716"> </a>If the difference between the minimum and maximum values detected is higher than 0.40 mm, replace the phonic wheel.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5718"> </a>Once checked that the difference is lower than or equal to 0.40 mm, carry out the shimming of the speed sensor (3) or (4)
            by the appropriate calibrated shims (B).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_012303248.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e5723"> </a>Phonic wheels cleaning
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5725"> </a>It is important to check that both phonic wheels (1) and (2) are always clean.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5727"> </a>Otherwise: gently remove any possible dirt deposits with a cloth or metal brush.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e5729"> </a>Avoid using solvents, abrasives and air or water jets directly on the phonic wheel (1) or (2).
         </div>
      </div>
